segment.source: From the Application Virtualization Server Management Console, you can generate a variety of reports that provide information about the system.
segment.target: From the Application Virtualization Server Management Console, you can generate a variety of reports that provide information about the system.

segment.source: This information includes usage information for applications and system error tracking.
segment.target: This information includes usage information for applications and system error tracking.

segment.source: Graphs the total daily usage, to help you determine the load on your Application Virtualization System.
segment.target: Graphs the total daily usage, to help you determine the load on your Application Virtualization System.

segment.source: Lists the usage information during the reporting period for all applications defined in the database, to help you determine which applications are the most heavily used.
segment.target: Lists the usage information during the reporting period for all applications defined in the database, to help you determine which applications are the most heavily used.

segment.source: Tracks usage information for a specified application, to help you determine how heavily a specific application is used.
segment.target: Tracks usage information for a specified application, to help you determine how heavily a specific application is used.

segment.source: Tracks the number of errors and warnings logged over time during the specified reporting period for the specified server or for the specified server group.
segment.target: Tracks the number of errors and warnings logged over time during the specified reporting period for the specified server or for the specified server group.
